<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p><code>libby</code> scrapes Library Genesis with <code>curl</code> and <code>pup</code> and gives you a list of downloads with <code>fzf</code>. I made this because I felt the alternatives were too slow. Feel free to add issues/feature requests/PRs!</p> <p>The tool is available on the AUR as <code>libby-git</code>.</p> <p><a href="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11081492/180638963-17bc20ca-e25e-47cc-8839-dd826be2eeef.gif">Demo</a></p> <p><a href="https://github.com/carterprince/libby">GitHub</a></p> <p><a href="https://github.com/carterprince/libby/blob/main/libby">Source</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Waste_Perception_233"> /u/Waste_Perception_233 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w6rv89/libby_a_simple_cli_tool_to_quickly_download_books/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w6rv89/libby_a_simple_cli_tool_to_quickly_download_books/">[comments]</a></span>